Motivation
------------------------------

Familiarize with git commands
Basic ideas should be 
Commands to be executed and see what happens
Understand what happens when i execute a command

Goal:
    know and understand basic commands
    be able to interact with other repositories
    understand neccessary steps to contribute to and OSS proj



Plan
------------------------------

setup:

    git config
        name
        email
        colors

introduce and practice basic commands:

    git clone
    git init 
    git add
    git commmit
    git log
    git diff
    git tag

introduce and practice advanced commands:

    git reset (--hard and --soft)
    git revert
    git branch
    git checkout
    git merge
    git rebase
    git cherry-pick

introduce and practice remote commands

    git fetch
    git push
    git pull
    git format-patch
    git send-email
    git am

show cool stuff

    git add -p
    git rebase -i
    git stash
    zsh vcs_info (grml-zsh setup)

Requirements:
------------------------------
Participants:
    laptop (linux bsd or solaris install, maybe mac)
    recent git (1.6 oslt)
    ssh-key (for interacting with server)
    irc-client (and know how to use it)

Organizers:
    publicly routable server, or only within the network (permanent is better)
    gitosis, git-web, gitdaemon, installed (for synchronizing users)
    ssh up and running


